ccess_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aCognitive Linguistics is an approach to language study based on the assumptions that our linguistic abilities are firmly rooted in our cognitive abilities, that meaning is essentially conceptualization, and that grammar is shaped by usage. The Handbook of Cognitive Linguistics provides state-of-the-art overviews of the numerous subfields of cognitive linguistics written by leading international experts which will be useful for established researchers and novices alike. It is an interdisciplinary project with contributions from linguists, psycholinguists, psychologists, and computer scientists which will emphasise the most recent developments in the field, in particular, the shift towards more empirically-based research. In this way, it will, we hope, help to shape the field, encouraging methodologically more rigorous research which incorporates insights from all the cognitive sciences. Editor Ewa Dąbrowska was awarded the Alexander von Humboldt Professorship 2018.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aCognitive grammarvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aCognitive grammarxHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aGerman languagevTextbooks for foreign speakers. 0aGerman languagexStudy and teachingxForeign speakers. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxTheoretical Frameworks and DisciplinesxCognitive Linguistics. 0aLinguistics and SemioticsxTheoretical Frameworks and DisciplinesxGeneral Linguistics. 0aLinguistics. 0aPsycholinguisticsvHandbooks, manuals, etc. 0aPsycholinguisticsxHandbooks, manuals, etc. 4aCognitive Linguistics, Usage-based Linguistics, Language, Mind and Culture. 4aKognitive Linguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aDabrowska, Ewa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDivjak, Dagmar, ee